arch:property.oc:show_val: Flot. sample 2 (4243), >4mm, 100%, diagnostics only A medium-size unit of medium to light brown bones. There is well under 5% burning and 2 -3% digestion. About a third of the unit is long bone fragments, which is a smaller proportion than normal. Additionally the fragment size is quite large with not a single piece of trampling or abrasion. The rest of the bones are limb bones, vertebra/ribs and skull bones in appoximately equal proportions. There are no pelvis or scapula fragments, this is not a preservation issue since there is a complete atlas and two almost complete hyoids. The unit looked rather different from the other fill units although it is difficult to pinpoint exactly what is distinct about it. There is one human phalanx with osteoarthritis and a broken bone point made from a sheep metapodial. The flotation sample is slightly different from the dry sieve. 20% of the material is burnt, but there is no digestion. There is a small amount of rolling and abrasion, but most is fairly clean and untrampled. There are a number of 02 vertebra fragments as well as the usual sheep/goat diagnostics. There is also a tiny fragment of a pig tooth. Last Number = 134

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
